Ph.D. Candidate (Master-to-Ph.D. transfer) in College of Cyberspace Security, University of Science and Technology of China (USTC), Hefei, China.

Research focus: LLM alignment.

Advisors: Prof. [https://imcc.ustc.edu.cn/_upload/tpl/0d/13/3347/template3347/zhangyongdong.html Yongdong Zhang], Prof. [https://faculty.ustc.edu.cn/maozhendong/zh_CN/index.htm Zhendong Mao].



Email: steviezhu1 at gmail.com

== About
I am a Ph.D. candidate at USTC focusing on alignment, safety, and trustworthy behavior of large language models. My work spans alignment training, robust optimization, and inference-time alignment. 

*I am currently on the job market.*

== Research Interests
- LLM alignment and safety
- Preference learning and reward modeling

